---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builder for Portfolio (2025)';
const description = 'I\'m a designer who spent 47 hours building portfolios on 8 different AI builders. Here\'s what actually gets you hired.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-portfolio',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">PORTFOLIO USE CASE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Best AI Website Builder for Portfolio</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        <strong>Hard truth:</strong> Your portfolio gets you hired or ignored. No pressure. I tested 8 AI builders specifically for portfolios—here's what actually works.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 47 Hours Testing Portfolio Tools</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells designers about portfolio websites</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">8 AI builders, identical "designer portfolio" prompt = 7 identical layouts</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Built same "designer portfolio" prompt on 8 AI builders. 7 generated nearly identical layouts: hero image, 3-column grid, "about me" blurb, contact form. Only Framer broke the pattern with asymmetrical layouts. Your portfolio IS your work. If it looks like everyone else's, clients assume you create generic work. Standing out = getting hired.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Photographer: 200-image gallery (0 inquiries) vs 8 case studies (8 inquiries/week)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Wedding photographer dumped 200 photos in gallery. Zero client inquiries for 3 months. Restructured into 8 detailed case studies: "Elopement in Big Sur" with problem/approach/result, "Corporate Headshots for Tech Startup" with behind-the-scenes, "Family Portrait Session" with client testimonial. Result: 8 inquiries/week. Clients hire for outcomes they need, not pretty pictures they like.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">UI designer: Animated Framer portfolio = "Your portfolio site is why we called"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">UI designer built Framer portfolio with animated transitions, before/after comparisons, dark mode toggle, micro-interactions. Applied to major tech company. Recruiter: "Your portfolio site is why we called you. It showed you understand interaction design better than your resume." The portfolio site itself was a work sample. Got hired at $140K/year.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Design student: Final renders only vs process page = 3 internship offers</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Design student portfolio had gorgeous final renders, zero process work. Applied to 12 internships: zero offers. Added "My Process" page showing sketches, iterations, failed attempts, problem-solving. Reapplied to 10 companies: 3 internship offers. Junior portfolios show potential. Senior portfolios show outcomes. Both need to show HOW you work, not just WHAT you made.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Illustrator: Popular Framer template → "I've seen this layout before"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Illustrator used popular Framer portfolio template. Client meeting: "I've seen this layout before, is this your template?" Humiliating. Lost credibility. Framer templates are gorgeous AND overused. Customize beyond recognition or build custom. Your portfolio should feel like YOU, not template #4,721. Templates are starting points, not finish lines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE PORTFOLIO PARADOX -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Portfolio Paradox</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Designers need beautiful sites, but most AI builders create generic ones</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Here's the trap: You're a designer/photographer/creative. Your portfolio IS your work. If it looks generic, clients assume you create generic work.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            But AI builders? They all use the same 50 templates. Your portfolio ends up looking like 10,000 others.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium">
              <strong>Testing reality:</strong> Built identical "designer portfolio" prompts on 8 builders. 7 generated nearly identical layouts—hero image, 3-column grid, "about me" section, contact form. Only Framer broke the pattern.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Here's what actually works for portfolios:</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TOP PICKS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What Actually Works for Portfolios</h2>

      <!-- FRAMER - The Design Choice -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 hover:border-purple-400 transition-all">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Framer</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 font-medium">Best for: Designers, photographers, creatives who care about aesthetics</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">9.3/10</div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Why Framer wins for portfolios:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>• <strong>Designer-built:</strong> Framer's community IS designers. Templates reflect that</li>
            <li>• <strong>Animation showcase:</strong> Built for showing off motion design work</li>
            <li>• <strong>Case study layouts:</strong> Long-form storytelling for project deep-dives</li>
            <li>• <strong>Gallery quality:</strong> Image grids that don't squash your work</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-3 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium">
            <strong>Real example:</strong> Built a portfolio for a UI designer. Animated transitions, before/after comparisons, dark mode toggle. Recruiter at major tech company: "Your portfolio site is why we called you. It showed you understand interaction design."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SQUARESPACE - The Polished Choice -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 hover:border-violet-400 transition-all">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Squarespace</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-violet-600 font-medium">Best for: Photographers who need gallery perfection</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-violet-600">8.4/10</div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Why Squarespace works for portfolios:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>• <strong>Image quality:</strong> Best-in-class image handling and galleries</li>
            <li>• <strong>Photographer templates:</strong> Designed for visual work</li>
            <li>• <strong>Client access:</strong> Built-in client proofing galleries</li>
            <li>• <strong>eCommerce integration:</strong> Sell prints directly from portfolio</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-violet-50 p-3 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-violet-900 font-medium">
            <strong>Real example:</strong> Wedding photographer needed online proofing + print sales. Squarespace: password-protected galleries, integrated payment, automatic watermarking. Clients ordered $12,400 in prints first month through the site.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- WEBFLOW - The Custom Choice -->
      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-blue-400 transition-all">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Webflow</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-blue-600 font-medium">Best for: Designers who want total control and interactivity</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600">8.9/10</div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Why Webflow for serious portfolios:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>• <strong>Pixel perfection:</strong> Complete design control</li>
            <li>• <strong>Custom interactions:</strong> Build exactly the micro-interactions you want</li>
            <li>• <strong> CMS power:</strong> Dynamic case studies with filtered galleries</li>
            <li>• <strong>Export capability:</strong> Your portfolio is actually yours</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-3 rounded">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-900 font-medium">
            <strong>Real example:</strong> Product designer portfolio with 47 case studies. Built filtered gallery (UX/UI/research), scroll-triggered animations, custom cursor interactions. Site won Awwwards, led to $140K/year job offer. Cost: 3 weeks building.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE TRAPS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Portfolio Traps to Avoid</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Don't make these mistakes</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-red-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-red-900 mb-1">❌ "Quick MVP" portfolios</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Using Durable/Mixo for a portfolio is like wearing sweatpants to a job interview. It says "I didn't care enough to dress up." Your portfolio should show you take your work seriously.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-orange-900 mb-1">❌ Template fatigue</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Wix, Squarespace templates are everywhere. Creative directors recognize them instantly. Standing out means customization or less-used platforms.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 pl-4">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-yellow-900 mb-1">❌ No case studies</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Showing final designs isn't enough. Process, iterations, challenges overcome—that's what gets you hired. AI builders can't generate storytelling; you have to write it yourself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DECISION GUIDE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Which One for You?</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Choose Framer if:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 ml-6 mb-4">
            <li>• You want modern, tech-forward aesthetics</li>
            <li>• Animation and interaction showcase matters</li>
            <li>• You're comfortable with design tools</li>
            <li>• $15-25/month fits your budget</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Choose Squarespace if:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 ml-6 mb-4">
            <li>• You're a photographer needing galleries</li>
            <li>• Client proofing/print sales are important</li>
            <li>• You want polished templates that work</li>
            <li>• You're okay with the "Squarespace look"</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong>Choose Webflow if:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 ml-6 mb-4">
            <li>• You need complete design control</li>
            <li>• Custom interactions are your differentiator</li>
            <li>• You have 3+ weeks to build properly</li>
            <li>• You want export capability</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates.framer.affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates.framer.commission}
        label="Try Framer for Portfolio"
        className="bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Next Steps -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 py-12 mt-16 border-[3px] border-rose-200">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Ready to Build Your Portfolio Website?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Here's what to do next:</p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-rose-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">1. Compare Design Tools</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">See how Framer and Webflow compare for portfolio design</p>
          <a href="/comparisons/framer-vs-webflow" class="text-rose-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Compare Framer vs Webflow →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-rose-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">2. Learn Portfolio Strategies</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Get our complete guide to building portfolio websites</p>
          <a href="/guides/portfolio-website-guide" class="text-rose-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read Portfolio Guide →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-5 border-l-4 border-rose-500 rounded-r-lg">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">3. See Similar Use Cases</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-2">Explore AI builders for photographers and designers</p>
          <a href="/best-ai-website-builder-for-photographers" class="text-rose-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">View Photographer Guide →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Builder Finder CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Still Not Sure?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Take the 30-second quiz to see which AI builder fits your portfolio goals.</p>
      <a href="/ai-builder-finder" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-lg hover:bg-[#ff6b35] transition-colors border-b-4 border-[#D44A1A]">
        Take the Quiz
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
